<dl id="n12140q"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12140q">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12140q"> 140(q)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ ginseng</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> The mystery society of the Ojibwa has been closely studied &hellip; In the third degree <font color="green">[of initiation]</font> use is made of <mark>ginseng</mark>, &ldquo;man root,&rdquo; which is supposed to be of &ldquo;divine&rdquo; origin. &hellip; Those who have passed into the third stage become powerful magicians, who derive their power from the sky, and often have sky spirits for &ldquo;familiars.&rdquo; <small> William James Perry, <a name="ORMR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ORMR"><cite title="source">Origin of Magic and Religion</cite></a> (1923) 153</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
